cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.MM

The paper discusses the role of social networks in promoting content on Digg, a social news aggregator. This falls under the category of social media and social networks, which is covered by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The paper also analyzes the spread of interest in news stories, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and cyber security (cs.CYBER) aspects. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of blog authoring tools and content distribution, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
